title: VicAI Launches 2026 Programme with Record Membership
summary: Victoria Artificial Intelligence Society opens the academic year with over 200 registered members and an expanded calendar of talks, workshops, and hackathons across Trimester 1.

title: VicAI Partners with Anthropic for AI Safety Workshop Series
summary: New partnership brings AI safety research expertise to Wellington students through a series of hands-on workshops at Kelburn Campus, beginning March 2026.

title: VicAI Hackathon 2025 Winners Announced
summary: Three student teams recognised for innovative AI solutions addressing public sector challenges in Aotearoa New Zealand. Over 80 participants competed across 24 hours.

title: VicAI Submits to Government Consultation on AI Regulation
summary: Student-led submission to the Ministry of Business, Innovation and Employment draws on perspectives from computer science, law, and te ao Maori.

title: VicAI and Xero Co-Host Industry Night on AI in Finance
summary: Wellington's tech community gathered at Kelburn Campus for a panel discussion on machine learning applications in financial technology, featuring Xero engineers and VUW researchers.
